---
import Layout from '@/components/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Programming Principles" description="Learn the foundational principles of effective rucking training and workout design">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8 text-center">Programming Principles</h1>
  <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-12 text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto">
    Effective rucking training follows specific principles that ensure safety, progression, and results. These guidelines help you design workouts that build endurance, strength, and resilience while minimizing injury risk.
  </p>
  
  <div class="grid gap-8">
    <!-- Principle 1: Progressive Overload -->
    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow border-l-4 border-red-800">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-red-800 flex items-center">
        <span class="bg-red-100 text-red-800 text-xs px-3 py-1 rounded mr-3">1</span>
        Progressive Overload
      </h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
        Gradually increase the demands on your body over time to continue making progress. This can be achieved by increasing weight, distance, duration, or intensity.
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-600">
        <li>Increase load by no more than 10% per week</li>
        <li>Add distance or time gradually (10-15% increases)</li>
        <li>Increase intensity before volume when possible</li>
        <li>Deload every 4-6 weeks to allow recovery</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    
    <!-- Principle 2: Specificity -->
    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow border-l-4 border-red-800">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-red-800 flex items-center">
        <span class="bg-red-100 text-red-800 text-xs px-3 py-1 rounded mr-3">2</span>
        Specificity
      </h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
        Train specifically for the demands you want to improve. Your body adapts to the specific stresses placed upon it.
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-600">
        <li>Train on terrain similar to your goals</li>
        <li>Practice with the load you'll carry in events</li>
        <li>Include movement patterns specific to rucking</li>
        <li>Train energy systems relevant to your target duration</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    
    <!-- Principle 3: Recovery -->
    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow border-l-4 border-red-800">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-red-800 flex items-center">
        <span class="bg-red-100 text-red-800 text-xs px-3 py-1 rounded mr-3">3</span>
        Recovery & Adaptation
      </h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
        Progress happens during recovery, not during the workout. Adequate rest is essential for adaptation and injury prevention.
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-600">
        <li>Include at least 1-2 rest days per week</li>
        <li>Alternate hard and easy training days</li>
        <li>Prioritize sleep (7-9 hours per night)</li>
        <li>Use active recovery like easy walks or mobility work</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    
    <!-- Principle 4: Individualization -->
    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow border-l-4 border-red-800">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-red-800 flex items-center">
        <span class="bg-red-100 text-red-800 text-xs px-3 py-1 rounded mr-3">4</span>
        Individualization
      </h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
        Training programs must be tailored to the individual. What works for one person may not work for another.
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-600">
        <li>Consider your current fitness level</li>
        <li>Account for injury history and limitations</li>
        <li>Adjust for available time and equipment</li>
        <li>Listen to your body's feedback</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    
    <!-- Principle 5: Variation -->
    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow border-l-4 border-red-800">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-red-800 flex items-center">
        <span class="bg-red-100 text-red-800 text-xs px-3 py-1 rounded mr-3">5</span>
        Variation
      </h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
        Vary your training stimuli to prevent plateaus and overuse injuries while maintaining consistent progress toward goals.
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-600">
        <li>Change routes and terrain regularly</li>
        <li>Vary load weights throughout the week</li>
        <li>Include different workout types (endurance, strength, speed)</li>
        <li>Periodically change workout structure and focus</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    
    <!-- Principle 6: Consistency -->
    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow border-l-4 border-red-800">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-red-800 flex items-center">
        <span class="bg-red-100 text-red-800 text-xs px-3 py-1 rounded mr-3">6</span>
        Consistency
      </h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
        Regular, consistent training yields better results than sporadic intense sessions. Build habits that support long-term progress.
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-600">
        <li>Aim for regular training frequency</li>
        <li>Build sustainable habits, not short-term fixes</li>
        <li>Track your workouts to see patterns</li>
        <li>Focus on long-term progression over quick fixes</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-center mb-6 text-red-800">Applying These Principles</h2>
    <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6">
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
        The workout generator on this site incorporates these principles by:
      </p>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-3 text-gray-600">
        <li>Providing scalable difficulty levels that follow progressive overload</li>
        <li>Including varied terrain and workout types for specificity</li>
        <li>Structuring workouts with adequate warmup and cooldown for recovery</li>
        <li>Allowing customization based on time preferences and difficulty</li>
        <li>Generating varied workouts to prevent adaptation plateaus</li>
        <li>Encouraging regular use through easy accessibility</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
